Developer: @vgoot
Code Review: @sung @kkeshava

[Description]
New access log appender reporting alog messages into '/var/log/ceph/access.log'.
New dpp logging subsystem 'alog' to facilitate access log reporting.
New reporting around LC processor to highlighting {bucket_name, lc_operation[lc_expire_current,lc_expire_noncurrent,lc_abort_mpu,lc_expire_dm], op_return_code] 
Access log file format must be sutable for Loki (log collection) subsytem. Loki is optimized for handling logs, and by using key-value pairs. 

Common Guidelines for Loki-Compatible Logs:
- Format the logs in a structured key-value pairs, which makes them easier to parse and query in Loki.
- The key-value pairs are space-separated.
- Use key-value pairs to allow easy querying with Loki's query language (LogQL).
- Timestamp in a standard format (ISO 8601 or RFC 3339) as Loki handles time-based queries.


[Logging]
New log file 
/var/log/ceph/ceph-client.rgw.${instance}.access.log
Grafana experimental:
https://grafana.linode.com/d/ednak6pnwuu4ge/vgoot-ceph-quincy-rgw-overview-copy?orgId=1&refresh=10s&editPanel=35

[Output]
LC processor Key-Value Pairs Example:
  time=2024-10-01T07:52:31Z timestamp=1727769151.265 bucket=test5 op=lc_expire_current ret=0

[Config]
  name: enable_accesslog
  type: bool
  level: basic
  desc: enable access log
  default: false

[Rollout]
The feature is disabled by default. To enable set 'enable_accesslog' variable to true.
  ceph config set client.rgw enable_accesslog true
LC reporting to the access log can also be disabled by setting the severity for the 'alog' subsystem to a value below 4.
  ceph config set client.rgw debug_alog 3

