JIRA https://track.akamai.com/jira/browse/CEPH-245

Developer: @vgoot
Code Review: @sung @kkeshava

[Description]
Customized dynamic resharding. 
Design document: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QhK2C_JdWWn-sMVEZ6nZFpYXICb9FlYO98a3g24BU_0/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.d1h1hwr22kco
When new 'rgw_reshard_direct_max' options is set and dynamic resharding enabled. RGW will switch to from dynamic resharding to a two-step resharding which ensure 
what resharding scales directly up to `rgw_max_dynamic_shards` once the shard density exceeds `rgw_max_objs_per_shard`. 

Note:
The two-step resharding mode, controlled by the rgw_reshard_direct_max option, is now the default resharding approach. To revert to dynamic resharding, disable this option.

Required Configuration Changes for Production and SQA:
1.Remove `rgw_override_bucket_index_max_shards = 1009`
  This option previously overrode the default shard value for newly created buckets.
  With its removal, new buckets will revert to the default setting of 11 shards upom creation. 
  It also capped max number of shards which now should be controlled by `rgw_max_dynamic_shards`.
2.Remove `rgw_dynamic_resharding = false`
  Previously, this setting disabled dynamic resharding.
  Its removal implicitly enables two-step resharding, which is now the default.
3.Update `rgw_max_dynamic_shards` to 1009
  The maximum number of shards will be capped at 1009, reduced from the default 1999, since rgw_override_bucket_index_max_shards has been removed.
4.Maintain `rgw_max_objs_per_shard` at the default threshold of 100,000
  This ensures the direct max jump threshold remains at ~1,100,000 objects (11 shards * 100,000).
5.Manually downshard all buckets with fewer than 1,000,000 objects to 11 shards
  $ radosgw-admin bucket stats | jq '.[] | {bucket,num_shards,"num_objects":.usage."rgw.main".num_objects} | select (.num_shards > 11 and .num_objects<1000000) | .bucket' | xargs -I []  radosgw-admin reshard add --bucket [] --num-shards 11 --yes-i-really-mean-it 

[Config]
- name: rgw_reshard_direct_max
  type: bool
  level: basic
  desc: Scale up to rgw_max_dynamic_shards once shard density exceeds rgw_max_objs_per_shard for the first time.
  long_desc: Alternative to dynamic resharding, if enabled RGW will switch from dynamic resgarding to a two-step approach.
    Initially, the number of shards is set to the minimum, then automatically scales up to `rgw_max_dynamic_shards`
    once the shard density surpasses `rgw_max_objs_per_shard` for the first time.
    The rgw_dynamic_resharding option must be also enabled for this mode to take effect.
  default: true
  services:
  - rgw
  see_also:
  - rgw_dynamic_resharding
  - rgw_max_objs_per_shard
  - rgw_max_dynamic_shards


