JIRA https://track.akamai.com/jira/browse/CEPH-188

Developer: @vgoot
Code Review: @sung @kkeshava

[Description]
RBD: overload protection
Design document: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1rPY99ewvNRIFQCxQ5NRAcRF8W2m4mTUdXKIlUDgE_io/edit?tab=t.0
Slack: https://linode.slack.com/archives/C07TM0UV06S/p1732881016164039

This implementation extends Ceph's OSD and MGR components with PSI-based CPU pressure monitoring and automated throttling.
- OSD Extension: Each OSD reports CPU pressure (cpu_psi) and idle CPU metrics (cpu_idle) through its admin socket.
- MGR PSI Plugin: The manager module collects these metrics from OSDs at a configurable interval (mgr/psi/interval) and evaluates cluster-wide CPU health.
- Automated Throttling: If the pressure metrics exceed defined thresholds on at least mgr/psi/trigger_count hosts, the cluster enters a throttled state. Throttling is lifted when CPU conditions improve across the same number of hosts.
- Cool-down Control: When mgr/psi/cooldown_seconds is set, the system enforces a delay before exiting the throttling state to avoid rapid toggling.
- Historical Logging: The module maintains a rolling history of the last 10 throttle activation and release events.
- Persistent State and Failover: Throttle state, configuration option and history are persisted, allowing the state to survive manager restarts or automatic failover to a standby MGR node which should resume PSI enforcement automatically after failover.
- Manual Controls: CLI commands (mgr psi throttle_on, mgr psi throttle_off) allow manual override of the throttling state regardless of system thresholds.
- Health Reporting: When active, the module adds a PSI_THROTTLE_ACTIVE warning to the Ceph health panel, including host count and timestamp.


[Logging]
MGR Plugin activity is logged into
  /var/log/ceph/ceph-mgr.<mgr_id>.log  (filter with grep psi)

It is possible to control log verbosity with:
  ceph config set mgr mgr/psi/log_level <debug|info|warning|error> 

[Commands]
CEPH commands:
  ceph -s       To check active MGR and throttling state in HEALTH dashboard 
  ceph health detail -f json-pretty | less
                To see more details of throtlling 
  ceph config get mgr mgr/psi/<option> 
                To get PSI option (see config section)
  ceph config set mgr mgr/psi/<option> <Value>
                To set PSI option (see config section) 
  ceph daemon <osd_id> psi
                To get PSI probe from admin socket 
  ceph config get osd bluestore_throttle_bytes              
                To check current throttling level
                
PSI CLI commands 
  mgr psi history            Show recent throttle history
  mgr psi throttle_on        Manually enable throttling
  mgr psi throttle_off       Manually disable throttling
  mgr psi snapshot           Retrieve the latest PSI sample
  mgr psi help               Show this help message

[Config]
  idle_cell_threshold       (float): Minimum CPU idle percent required to exit throttling (0 disables check) [default=15.0]
  idle_floor_threshold      (float): Maximum CPU idle percent to allow triggering throttling (0 disables check) [default=7.0]
  trigger_count             (int): Number of hosts that must meet condition to trigger or stop throttling [default=10]
  throttle_bytes            (str): Value to set for bluestore_throttle_bytes when enabling throttle [default=10000]
  interval                  (int): Interval (in seconds) between CPU checks [default=60]
  start_avg300_threshold    (float): Threshold for avg300 to trigger config change [default=80.0]
  stop_avg300_threshold     (float): avg300 threshold below which throttle is removed [default=50.0]
  stop_avg60_threshold      (float): avg60 threshold below which throttle is removed [default=40.0]
  cooldown_seconds          (int): Cool-down time (in seconds) after throttle removal to avoid flipping [default=600]

{Notes]
It is possible to enable and disable this extension with 
  ceph mgr module disable psi
  ceph mgr module enable psi
In event of disabling the current throttle state will be preserved (and restored if the module is re-enabled later) unless manually reset. To clear throttle state manually:
  ceph mgr psi throttle_off

